31:28.970 --> 31:31.314
You're gonna be alright.
Alright.

31:31.473 --> 31:33.771
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERS)</font>

31:45.112 --> 31:47.130
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGS)</font>
Listen. I need to take the antiques!

31:47.155 --> 31:49.408
You don't need to do anything!
They were in my family!

31:49.574 --> 31:51.301
They belong to me.
Your family? Your family?

31:51.326 --> 31:54.250
That desk was from Marie Antoinette!
Oh, please!

31:54.413 --> 31:56.131
It's a fake! Yes. it was!

31:56.289 --> 31:58.838
<font color="#808080">WOMAN ON PHONE:</font> <i>I'm sorry, sir.
No one picked up.</i>

31:59.000 --> 32:02.049
<i>Is there another number
you'd like to try?</i>

32:02.212 --> 32:04.089
Um...

32:04.256 --> 32:07.055
No, no. That's OK.

32:07.217 --> 32:09.595
That's fine. Thank you.

32:12.180 --> 32:14.433
I think it's a pretty good
pairing over there.

32:14.599 --> 32:15.976
Mm-hm.

32:16.143 --> 32:19.898
She's very, uh,
opinionated and judgemental.

32:20.063 --> 32:23.693
Yeah. <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS AWKWARDLY)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

32:25.026 --> 32:28.280
I told you this was a bad idea.
Shut up. Shut up.

32:31.825 --> 32:34.954
<font color="#D900D9">(CHOPIN'S <i>NOCTURNE</i> Op. 9 No.2)</font>

32:36.496 --> 32:38.043
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS FRENCH)</font>

33:00.270 --> 33:02.898
<font color="#D900D9">(SLAMS DOOR)</font>
Well, then, tell me about him!

33:03.064 --> 33:04.441
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN STAMMERS)</font> Seriously?

33:04.608 --> 33:07.782
Yes, seriously! Of course!
Here I am. I'm listening.

33:07.944 --> 33:10.038
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Is... is this a joke?

33:10.197 --> 33:12.700
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> What a pitiful
advocate you are.

33:12.866 --> 33:15.540
Speak whether it's a joke or not!

33:15.702 --> 33:19.502
Uhh, why are you looking
all around the room like that?

33:19.664 --> 33:22.884
Oh, you... you really
are in a temper!

33:23.043 --> 33:24.636
I wish to take a lover, Octave,

33:24.794 --> 33:26.842
or if not a lover
at least a cavalier.

33:27.005 --> 33:29.474
Whom do you suggest?
I shall abide by your choice.

33:29.633 --> 33:31.601
From tomorrow... from this evening,

33:31.760 --> 33:35.481
whoever has a fancy to sing beneath
my window will find my door ajar.

33:35.639 --> 33:37.892
Well...
Well?! Nothing to say?

33:38.058 --> 33:40.186
Marry me!

33:40.352 --> 33:43.652
<font color="#D900D9">(APPLAUSE)</font>

33:51.905 --> 33:53.623
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

33:55.200 --> 33:57.749
Sure don't like the way
you were looking at Dylan tonight.

33:57.911 --> 33:59.538
I am not doing anything!

33:59.704 --> 34:02.127
OK, maybe it's me, but I don't know.

34:02.290 --> 34:04.292
Just stop it.

34:06.545 --> 34:07.922
I don't know.

34:08.088 --> 34:10.106
I didn't even understand
any of the Parisian speak.

34:10.130 --> 34:12.179
I think they were Canadian.

34:14.803 --> 34:16.603
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <i>Bonsoir, Monsieur Valmont.</i>
Hello, Didier.

34:16.763 --> 34:19.232
Your usual table is waiting.
Great. Thank you.

34:19.391 --> 34:22.815
Uh, will you be paying tonight
or putting it on the books?

34:22.978 --> 34:24.446
It will be on the books.

34:24.603 --> 34:26.606
And that goes for
the whole table, so...

34:26.773 --> 34:29.525
Ahh, very well.
Please, right this way.

34:29.693 --> 34:31.239
Shall we? It's just down here.

34:31.402 --> 34:33.280
<i>S'il vous plaît. Bonsoir.</i>

34:33.446 --> 34:35.039
Yes.

34:36.574 --> 34:38.043
<font color="#D900D9">(CLICKS)</font>

34:38.201 --> 34:40.203
It's just a little bit.
I'll just have a little.

34:40.370 --> 34:42.168
What did you think?
I don't know.

34:42.330 --> 34:44.003
I felt that it was
sort of pretentious.

34:44.165 --> 34:46.007
It seemed like everyone
who was in the theatre

34:46.167 --> 34:47.668
was just there to be seen.

34:47.835 --> 34:49.304
There to be seen?

34:49.462 --> 34:51.635
It was a theatre.
It was pitch black in there.

34:51.797 --> 34:55.052
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> How am I supposed to care

34:55.217 --> 34:57.846
about a group of
over-privileged affluent types

34:58.013 --> 35:00.607
who go gallivanting around without
any sort of a moral compass?

35:00.765 --> 35:02.859
The affluent have plenty
of problems. I'm a mess.

35:03.018 --> 35:06.067
I'm sorry, but I'm very sensitive
to an audience's reaction

35:06.229 --> 35:07.856
and I couldn't get into it.

35:08.023 --> 35:10.276
If they all jumped off a bridge,
would you join them?

35:10.442 --> 35:11.944
I hate that analogy. I really do.

35:12.110 --> 35:14.329
But maybe. Maybe there's a reason
why they're all doing that.

35:14.487 --> 35:16.831
Maybe the bridge is about
to explode and no one told me.

35:16.990 --> 35:19.084
That's a good point.
I'm just...

35:19.242 --> 35:22.291
How am I supposed to sympathise
with these characters?

35:22.454 --> 35:24.707
No one suffers any consequences
for their actions,

35:24.873 --> 35:27.717
no one learns anything
and nobody changes.

35:28.752 --> 35:31.301
It was a satire.

35:31.463 --> 35:33.340
I didn't get that at all.

35:33.506 --> 35:37.477
I love this place. It's so chic.
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> Wait.

35:37.636 --> 35:40.936
I thought you said that
the door policy was discriminatory

35:41.097 --> 35:42.724
and this place was insipid.

35:42.891 --> 35:46.816
Oh, I did say that,
but that was before I came inside.

35:46.978 --> 35:48.446
Uh-huh.

35:48.605 --> 35:52.781
I'm gonna go.
Count to five and then follow me.

35:52.942 --> 35:56.697
<font color="#808080">JOCELYN:</font> Ooh! <font color="#D900D9">(COUGHS)</font>
Are you wearing perfume?

35:56.863 --> 35:58.240
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> Excuse me?

35:58.406 --> 36:00.759
<font color="#808080">JOCELYN:</font> Don't you feel
a bit strange about being an artist

36:00.784 --> 36:02.582
in a world that's
already so full of art?

36:02.744 --> 36:04.291
Isn't that sort of a waste?

36:04.454 --> 36:05.922
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> I forget. What do you do?

36:06.081 --> 36:07.849
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font> I'm getting
a doctorate at Columbia

36:07.874 --> 36:09.922
is postmodern criticism.

36:10.085 --> 36:12.929
For me, I think that people who are
creative are really just indulgent.

36:13.088 --> 36:15.841
There's already so much.
We don't need any more.

36:16.007 --> 36:18.351
And there are so many people
who are without, you know?

36:18.510 --> 36:21.138
You should... just be a farmer.

36:21.304 --> 36:23.448
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> You can always tell
what someone thinks of you

36:23.473 --> 36:24.941
by who they set you up with.

36:25.100 --> 36:27.102
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

36:29.020 --> 36:31.443
The only reason that
I'm dancing with you

36:31.606 --> 36:33.904
is because I'm incredibly drunk.

36:34.067 --> 36:37.071
I despise you
and everything that you stand for.

36:37.237 --> 36:38.955
Where are Conrad and Beatrice?

36:39.114 --> 36:42.914
I don't know. Do you wanna
get another drink? <font color="#D900D9">(SLURPS)</font>

36:44.744 --> 36:47.964
You're a bit of a philistine,
aren't you?

36:50.875 --> 36:52.548
I'm sorry. Wait.
Tell me your name again.

36:52.711 --> 36:54.179
Jocelyn.
Are you kidding me?

36:54.337 --> 36:56.681
I just got out of a three-year
relationship with a Jocelyn.

36:56.840 --> 36:58.513
Do you wanna sleep over?

36:58.675 --> 37:00.268
Mm, your place or mine?

37:00.427 --> 37:02.600
I live in a dorm.

37:04.264 --> 37:06.437
Definitely mine.

37:06.599 --> 37:08.351
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES)</font> Ooh!

37:08.518 --> 37:11.647
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT ROMANTIC MUSIC)</font>

37:12.689 --> 37:15.238
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> You know, I realised
something the other day.

37:15.400 --> 37:18.404
Usually the women that
I like as human beings,

37:18.570 --> 37:20.038
I'm not sexually attracted to

37:20.196 --> 37:22.073
and the ones that
I'm sexually attracted to

37:22.240 --> 37:25.619
I don't particularly like
as human beings.

37:25.785 --> 37:29.585
On the rare occasion when one of them
falls into both categories

37:29.748 --> 37:32.672
they usually have
a boyfriend or a husband.

37:32.834 --> 37:34.757
What are you trying to say?

37:34.919 --> 37:37.422
I'm trying to say...

37:37.589 --> 37:42.345
What I'm trying to say is it's great
that you don't have a boyfriend.

37:42.510 --> 37:45.855
Oh, but I am married.
Is that a problem?

37:46.014 --> 37:47.516
You're a cheater, though.

37:47.682 --> 37:49.525
Right? Oh, yeah.

38:03.281 --> 38:06.251
<font color="#D900D9">(ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES)</font>

38:13.041 --> 38:15.339
<font color="#D900D9">(CLOCK TICKS)</font>

38:18.671 --> 38:21.971
<font color="#D900D9">(INHALES AND EXHALES HEAVILY)</font>

38:23.051 --> 38:25.679
I gotta tell Dylan.

38:36.689 --> 38:39.408
<font color="#D900D9">(MURMURS HAPPILY)</font>

38:39.567 --> 38:42.446
<font color="#D900D9">(FOOTSTEPS RECEDE)</font>

38:42.612 --> 38:45.365
I've gotta tell him, right?
I mean, tell him.

38:45.532 --> 38:49.878
Just tell him right out
and you just... just let him know.

38:50.036 --> 38:52.710
You just tell him. Gotta tell him.

38:52.872 --> 38:55.716
You gotta tell him. Gotta tell him.

38:57.961 --> 39:00.214
You gotta tell him.

39:02.173 --> 39:04.346
Oh, God.

39:06.719 --> 39:08.437
<i>This was it.</i>

39:08.596 --> 39:11.349
<i>This was the moment Conrad
would right his wrongs.</i>

39:11.516 --> 39:13.314
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> Hey.

39:13.476 --> 39:16.195
<i>This was the moment he would
bare his soul to his only friend...</i>

39:16.354 --> 39:17.401
What's going on?

39:17.564 --> 39:19.908
<i>...and tell him of his betrayal.</i>

39:20.066 --> 39:24.242
<i>This was the moment Conrad
would ask for forgiveness.</i>

39:26.364 --> 39:28.037
Nothing.

39:28.199 --> 39:29.746
Nothing. Nothing at all.

39:29.909 --> 39:32.128
What? Does something
seem like it's going on?

39:33.288 --> 39:35.541
Yeah, it seemed like you were
about to say something.

39:35.707 --> 39:38.301
No. Uh-uh. No, no, not at all.
Where's the friend?

39:38.459 --> 39:40.962
Oh, you mean Jocelyn?

39:41.129 --> 39:44.929
No, the friend.
Yeah, the friend's name is Jocelyn.

39:45.091 --> 39:46.889
Oh, really? Ironic.
Yeah.

39:47.051 --> 39:49.520
I don't wanna talk about it.
Didn't have sex with her, huh?

39:49.679 --> 39:52.808
No, I didn't have sex with her.
I had to talk to her all night.

39:52.974 --> 39:54.442
She only left half an hour ago.

39:54.601 --> 39:56.319
It was horrible.

39:56.477 --> 39:59.026
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGS)</font>

39:59.188 --> 40:00.565
So, what happened last night?

40:00.732 --> 40:02.609
<font color="#808080">JOCELYN:</font> <i>What happened
was that it was amazing</i>

40:02.775 --> 40:04.527
<i>and we talked until the sun came up!</i>

40:04.694 --> 40:06.913
That's amazing!

40:07.071 --> 40:08.914
<font color="#D900D9">(SHORT PIANO PRELUDE)</font>

40:09.073 --> 40:11.292
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> I have something
I have to ask you.

40:11.451 --> 40:12.953
Yes.

40:13.119 --> 40:15.121
Are you sleeping with Beatrice?

40:15.288 --> 40:18.258
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

40:19.292 --> 40:20.919
Oh...

40:24.714 --> 40:26.091
No.

40:26.257 --> 40:27.850
Ohh...
No.

40:28.009 --> 40:29.682
Good.

40:29.844 --> 40:32.347
Good man.

40:32.513 --> 40:34.390
There's something
I'd like to ask you.

40:34.557 --> 40:36.730
May I sleep with Beatrice?

40:36.893 --> 40:41.069
Definitely not. No.

40:41.230 --> 40:42.857
I've got something
I'd like to tell you.

40:43.024 --> 40:45.126
What is it now?
Beatrice and I are already together.

40:45.151 --> 40:48.246
Hey, Dylan, Dylan! Easy, easy!
I'll fucking kill you!

40:48.404 --> 40:49.781
Now, as we ease into adulthood

40:49.948 --> 40:52.167
sometimes a good stiff drink
is the only excuse we have

40:52.325 --> 40:54.248
for committing the atrocities
we really want to.

40:54.410 --> 40:57.004
"Ease into adulthood"?
We're nearly 40!

40:57.163 --> 40:59.382
Careful. I said I was sorry, OK?
I was gonna...

40:59.540 --> 41:01.668
You're a selfish asshole.

41:01.834 --> 41:03.882
Now, hang on.

41:06.589 --> 41:09.593
Selfish? Dylan,
you're the one that's selfish.

41:09.759 --> 41:12.308
I might actually
have a shot with her, OK?

41:12.470 --> 41:15.189
She could be... the one.

41:15.348 --> 41:17.692
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font> "The one"!

41:17.850 --> 41:20.649
What are you, 14?
It's not charming anymore, Conrad.

41:20.812 --> 41:22.860
I need you to sleep
somewhere else tonight.

41:23.022 --> 41:24.990
You're kicking me out?

41:30.613 --> 41:33.958
And you realise by kicking me out
I'll probably move in with Beatrice?

41:39.205 --> 41:42.379
Sometimes you're
your own worst enemy.

41:50.717 --> 41:52.515
<i>Conrad's ability to trust</i>

41:52.677 --> 41:56.056
<i>had been marred by years
of betrayal and deceit</i>

41:56.222 --> 41:58.850
<i>for others had only
dated or befriended him</i>

41:59.017 --> 42:01.736
<i>to gain access to his wealth.</i>

42:01.894 --> 42:04.113
<i>He had been quoted
on numerous occasions</i>

42:04.272 --> 42:07.276
<i>as saying that no one
could be trusted.</i>

42:07.442 --> 42:12.414
<i>What he forgot to add was
that included himself.</i>

42:22.749 --> 42:24.296
Well, I feel very, very conflicted.

42:24.459 --> 42:26.928
I like the idea of living
up at the summer home.

42:27.086 --> 42:29.839
You know, upstate, life of
a reclusive writer. I really do.

42:30.006 --> 42:33.055
But I'm allergic
to the grass, the clean air,

42:33.217 --> 42:37.814
the bees, the ticks, the badgers,
a bunch of wildlife.

42:38.848 --> 42:41.271
What are you trying to say, Conrad?

42:41.434 --> 42:42.936
I am gonna move in with Beatrice.

42:43.102 --> 42:46.481
Ohh! Oh, that's great news.
Thank you.

42:46.647 --> 42:49.696
Does she know that you're broke
and have no place else to go?

42:49.859 --> 42:51.736
Huh!

42:54.280 --> 42:55.998
Of... Yes.

42:56.157 --> 42:58.876
Don't you feel guilty about Dylan?
Obviously.

42:59.035 --> 43:01.163
But, you know,
this is actually a very small city

43:01.329 --> 43:03.627
and if you meet an attractive girl,
the chances are great

43:03.790 --> 43:06.509
that one of your friends has
already slept with her or wants to.

43:06.667 --> 43:10.717
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font> You're lying
to yourself, Conrad.

43:10.880 --> 43:12.473
I know.

43:13.508 --> 43:15.055
I'm OK with it.

43:19.680 --> 43:22.183
Ding-dong! <font color="#D900D9">(PRESSES BUZZER)</font>

43:24.560 --> 43:27.860
Hi.
<i>Bonjour, Mon amour.</i>

43:28.022 --> 43:30.775
What's going on?
I'm moving in.

43:31.818 --> 43:33.741
What happened to Dylan's?

43:33.903 --> 43:36.702
I was allergic to his sheets
Egyptian cotton.

43:36.864 --> 43:39.333
I have Egyptian cotton.

43:40.368 --> 43:42.837
Well, we'll have to do
something about that.

43:45.790 --> 43:48.794
<font color="#D900D9">(CONRAD SIGHS)</font>

43:50.920 --> 43:52.888
I think I'm in love with you.

43:53.047 --> 43:55.516
How? It's only been two days.

43:57.176 --> 43:59.395
Then I'm in love
with the idea of you.

43:59.554 --> 44:01.556
Not the actual me?

44:01.722 --> 44:04.191
Well, the idea of someone's
always better.

44:06.602 --> 44:09.446
You can't have sex with an idea.

44:09.605 --> 44:12.654
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERFUL MUSIC)</font>

44:53.316 --> 44:56.286
I'm telling you,
don't put a scratch on it.

44:56.444 --> 44:59.243
I won't.
Your father is going to kill me.

44:59.405 --> 45:01.203
She's waiting.

45:02.408 --> 45:05.537
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC CONTINUES)</font>

45:19.884 --> 45:21.511
Come on!

45:29.977 --> 45:31.729
<font color="#D900D9">(BEATRICE SQUEALS)</font>

45:31.896 --> 45:33.944
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> OK. Look alive.

45:45.368 --> 45:48.292
Oh, there it is.

45:48.454 --> 45:50.252
Yeah? What do you see there?

45:50.414 --> 45:52.542
Well, I mean, it's obvious, kind of.

45:52.708 --> 45:54.301
Right.

45:54.460 --> 45:57.805
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> Explosive. It's explosive.

45:57.964 --> 46:00.558
A car, right?

46:02.134 --> 46:05.729
Do you see the...
You see just the headlights?

46:05.888 --> 46:07.811
It's a female orgasm.

46:07.974 --> 46:10.602
I think it's kind of clear.
I didn't...

46:10.768 --> 46:12.566
That the driver is having?

46:14.230 --> 46:16.528
<font color="#D900D9">(BEATRICE LAUGHS)</font>

46:19.527 --> 46:21.370
What's wrong?

46:21.529 --> 46:25.750
Um... nothing.

46:38.004 --> 46:41.679
<font color="#D900D9">(SINGLE PIANO NOTE PLAYS)</font>

46:43.926 --> 46:47.396
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES TO PLAY SAME NOTE,
THEN STOPS)</font>

46:55.646 --> 47:00.322
<i>Sitting at Beatrice's piano,
Conrad quietly read Dylan's note.</i>

47:00.484 --> 47:03.488
<i>"In lieu of
unnecessary explanations,"</i>

47:03.654 --> 47:05.873
<i>"please enjoy this Volvo."</i>

47:06.032 --> 47:09.957
<i>Conrad began to feel
an odd sensation</i>

47:10.119 --> 47:11.792
<i>one of guilt.</i>

47:11.954 --> 47:15.299
<i>He had never felt
the emotion before.</i>

47:20.004 --> 47:21.631
I think I have a brain tumour.

47:23.215 --> 47:24.808
What?

47:27.803 --> 47:29.521
Nothing.

47:31.849 --> 47:34.853
<font color="#D900D9">(WATER SPLASHES)</font>

47:41.984 --> 47:45.238
Mmm. I'm not... I'm not in the mood.
I'm sorry.

47:46.906 --> 47:48.783
Sorry. Sorry.

47:48.949 --> 47:53.170
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font> You're never
in the mood anymore.

47:53.329 --> 47:55.707
We had sex last night.

47:55.873 --> 48:01.505
Yeah. You seemed a little distant.

48:03.714 --> 48:05.808
Oh, we're just going
through a dry spell.

48:05.966 --> 48:08.515
Dry spell?
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> That's all.

48:10.471 --> 48:14.317
It's only been a week.

48:43.921 --> 48:47.846
<i>Watching Beatrice
as she delicately played the piano,</i>

48:48.008 --> 48:51.763
<i>Conrad felt horrible
for his ceaseless deception.</i>

48:51.929 --> 48:55.729
<i>For a moment, he contemplated
admitting his impoverishment.</i>

48:55.891 --> 48:59.691
<i>Then the moment passed.</i>

48:59.854 --> 49:01.948
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES TO PLAY)</font>

49:06.735 --> 49:08.237
I mean, how can I be with someone

49:08.404 --> 49:10.907
that doesn't appreciate
<i>Bach</i> or a <i>Valmont</i> ?

49:11.073 --> 49:16.546
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> This is a classic story,
Conrad. <i>"Pygmalion".</i>

49:16.704 --> 49:20.504
Have you even read <i>"Pygmalion"</i> ? This
has nothing to do with <i>"Pygmalion".</i>

49:20.666 --> 49:22.668
You should revisit that.

49:22.835 --> 49:26.055
Or get the notes
or I'll read it to you.

49:26.213 --> 49:29.308
I've seen "My Fair Lady".

49:29.467 --> 49:32.141
<font color="#808080">PHOTOGRAPHER:</font> OK,
Beatrice, stop right there.

49:32.303 --> 49:34.647
Don't move. OK.
Don't move. Like that.

49:34.805 --> 49:36.728
<font color="#D900D9">(CAMERA CLICKS)</font>
Beautiful, you're beautiful.

49:36.891 --> 49:39.815
Tu es magnifique, tu es splendide.
Ne bouge pas! Ne bouge pas!

49:39.977 --> 49:43.026
Regarde-moi. Give me love.
Give me love. Voilà. Comme ça.

49:43.189 --> 49:46.864
Do you love me? Smile. Ah. Voilà.

49:47.026 --> 49:49.996
You love me? You love me?
OK, show me. Show me.

49:50.154 --> 49:53.624
Show me you love me.
Show me. OK! Love!

49:53.782 --> 49:56.456
Hate! Now. Like that.
Beautiful, beautiful.

49:56.619 --> 50:01.500
Love. Hate. Love.

50:01.665 --> 50:03.588
Voilà! Encore une. One more.

50:04.793 --> 50:06.420
Chapter One.

50:06.587 --> 50:10.888
Greece was a place he'd visited
many times in his mind.

50:11.050 --> 50:13.644
But on this day...

50:19.308 --> 50:21.731
Jumping forward. Chapter three.

50:25.523 --> 50:27.275
Chapter four.

50:35.866 --> 50:39.621
So how long are they going to be
remodelling the Valmont?

50:42.122 --> 50:44.250
Ah... a couple of months maybe.
What?

50:44.416 --> 50:46.310
I think. Sometimes they take
a couple of months.

50:46.335 --> 50:49.339
You said weeks.
Well... Oh.

50:51.006 --> 50:54.306
Hey. I got your gift.
Hey.

50:54.468 --> 50:56.015
Mmm.

51:02.476 --> 51:06.447
Well, as good as it is to bump
into you guys, I have to go.

51:06.605 --> 51:07.982
I've got my opening tonight.

51:08.148 --> 51:11.368
What part of town's that in?
Whitman Gallery.

51:11.527 --> 51:16.328
Maybe we'll see you there.
Don't know if I... Time.

51:19.410 --> 51:21.378
Who's that girl?

51:22.955 --> 51:24.628
Jocelyn.
That's not Jocelyn.

51:24.790 --> 51:28.465
Ah, no. The... the other Jocelyn.
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES)</font>

51:28.627 --> 51:30.971
Let's get in this car. Come on.

51:31.130 --> 51:34.259
<font color="#D900D9">(<i>AIR ON THE G STRING</i>
BY BACH PLAYS)</font>

52:26.644 --> 52:28.567
I gotta go.

53:08.977 --> 53:11.071
<font color="#D900D9">(FAINT LAUGHTER)</font>

53:19.154 --> 53:21.373
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS INAUDIBLY)</font>

53:21.532 --> 53:24.285
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

53:51.103 --> 53:55.574
<i>Conrad had often professed
that he led a "life of the mind".</i>

53:55.733 --> 53:59.829
<i>Unfortunately for him,
his mind had been damaged</i>

53:59.987 --> 54:01.489
<i>by years of abandonment,</i>

54:01.655 --> 54:06.877
<i>philandering, Tom Collins, and
a two-pack-per-day nicotine habit,</i>

54:07.035 --> 54:10.130
<i>not to mention
an unhealthy Oedipal complex.</i>

54:10.289 --> 54:13.463
<i>The weight of his guilt
had finally become too heavy.</i>

54:13.625 --> 54:16.970
<i>The incessant charade
could go on no longer.</i>

54:27.973 --> 54:30.067
What's wrong?
Where were you?

54:30.225 --> 54:33.024
You left me in the concert.

54:33.187 --> 54:34.814
You stayed, huh?

54:34.980 --> 54:38.405
Actually, I did. It was beautiful.

54:44.239 --> 54:45.616
We're out of cigarettes.

54:45.783 --> 54:48.787
<font color="#D900D9">(FAST PACED DRUM MUSIC)</font>

54:48.952 --> 54:50.750
Where are we going?

54:50.913 --> 54:54.258
To the Valmont.

54:54.416 --> 54:55.884
Why are we hiding
behind the bushes?

54:56.043 --> 54:58.842
I want you to follow me on
the count of three. Ready? Go!

54:59.004 --> 55:00.722
<font color="#808080">BEATRICE:</font> What? Mmm.

55:00.881 --> 55:03.100
Hi, Timothy.
Fredrick.

55:03.258 --> 55:04.805
I don't believe
you're supposed to...

55:06.553 --> 55:12.105
Mr. Valmont? Mr. Valmont?
Mr. Valmont! Stop them!

55:12.267 --> 55:13.644
<font color="#D900D9">(LIFT DINGS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

55:13.811 --> 55:17.691
What is going on? This is crazy.
I know. Isn't it fun?

55:17.856 --> 55:19.483
Where are we going?

55:19.650 --> 55:21.778
What? Why are we...?

55:21.944 --> 55:23.537
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Shhhh!

55:23.695 --> 55:25.447
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)</font>

55:25.614 --> 55:27.412
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Come on!

55:31.578 --> 55:32.500
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR SLAMS)</font>

55:32.663 --> 55:34.823
<font color="#808080">BEATRICE:</font> Please turn on the lights.
What is happening?

55:34.957 --> 55:37.927
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> It's a game. Hey, if you see
my mother's jewels, get those.

55:38.085 --> 55:40.053
<font color="#808080">BEATRICE:</font> What?
No, we should not do that.

55:40.212 --> 55:42.010
Yeah, we should.
<font color="#D900D9">(OBJECTS RATTLE)</font>

55:43.465 --> 55:44.967
Huh?

55:45.133 --> 55:47.431
I showed her,
that washed-up debutante.

55:47.594 --> 55:48.720
<font color="#D900D9">(LIFT DINGS)</font>

55:51.598 --> 55:53.396
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

55:54.434 --> 55:55.811
Shit.

55:55.978 --> 55:57.901
Really, really good work, Timothy.

55:58.063 --> 55:59.656
It's Fredrick, sir.

55:59.815 --> 56:03.240
Yes, Fredrick. Sorry. No, I think you
lot are really picking up the pace.

56:03.402 --> 56:05.450
You know where to return
Mother's jewels, right?

56:05.612 --> 56:09.662
That's the penthouse, the East Wing,
the Rhodesian cabinet, third drawer.

56:09.825 --> 56:11.498
I've got my cigarettes.

56:11.660 --> 56:15.085
<font color="#D900D9">(LOWERS HIS VOICE)</font> Please
tell Bernard that I'm very sorry.

56:17.583 --> 56:20.006
I'll be right there, honey.

56:22.087 --> 56:24.306
<font color="#808080">BEATRICE:</font> What was all that about?

56:24.464 --> 56:27.013
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> I'm not sure
I even know anymore.

56:27.175 --> 56:29.098
Conrad, what is going on?

56:29.261 --> 56:30.934
You know, Beatrice,

56:31.096 --> 56:34.066
I only moved in with you because
I've got no place else to go.

56:34.224 --> 56:36.022
OK, I'm broke.
What do you mean?

56:36.184 --> 56:37.652
I have nothing.

56:37.811 --> 56:40.530
I was kicked out of the Valmont,
parents cut me off.

56:40.689 --> 56:42.737
Conrad, you're nearly 40 years old.

56:42.900 --> 56:44.447
Well, that's completely irrelevant.

56:44.610 --> 56:46.157
I've got separation anxiety,
abandonment issues.

56:46.320 --> 56:48.994
Are you saying you've been lying
to me this entire time?

56:49.156 --> 56:53.411
Yes, but I'm not the only liar.

56:53.577 --> 56:55.796
I saw you with Dylan earlier today.

56:55.954 --> 56:58.753
What? You've been following me now?

57:00.083 --> 57:04.930
I... I was trying to patch things
up between you. God, grow up.

57:05.088 --> 57:07.637
You are not honest with yourself.
That's your problem.

57:07.799 --> 57:09.676
OK, you're always acting so virtuous.

57:09.843 --> 57:12.483
You're always talking about how
you want to be a bohemian musician.

57:12.596 --> 57:14.564
In the end, you're just a model.

57:14.723 --> 57:18.478
Well, at least I have a job.

57:18.644 --> 57:20.487
You have just managed
to coast through life

57:20.646 --> 57:23.399
without worrying about money or
anything else pertaining to reality.

57:23.565 --> 57:25.738
You are just
a philandering narcissist

57:25.901 --> 57:28.495
who's so afraid of being alone
because when you are alone,

57:28.654 --> 57:30.497
you're gonna realise
how empty your life is.

57:30.656 --> 57:32.158
You know what?
I should've gone with Dylan.

57:32.324 --> 57:35.578
Between the two of you, he was
the nice one. You are insufferable.

57:35.744 --> 57:38.167
Didn't seem to bother you
when I was flipping the bill.

57:38.330 --> 57:40.708
Alright, you're just like
the rest of them.

57:40.874 --> 57:42.501
You were only with me for the money.

57:42.668 --> 57:44.796
I am the only girl
you have ever been with

57:44.962 --> 57:46.555
who wasn't just in it
for the money.

57:46.713 --> 57:48.431
And besides, you were broke.

57:51.301 --> 57:55.681
Well... you didn't know that, so...

57:59.059 --> 58:02.188
<font color="#D900D9">(ELEGANT PIANO MUSIC)</font>

59:29.107 --> 59:31.155
<font color="#D900D9">(HORN HONKS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECH)</font>

59:35.322 --> 59:38.542
<i>Staring into the grille
of a bread truck,</i>

59:38.700 --> 59:41.544
<i>Conrad couldn't help
but think of the poor woman</i>

59:41.703 --> 59:46.174
<i>who had been diagnosed with
Witzelsucht, the joking disease.</i>

59:46.333 --> 59:51.180
<i>In a daze, he suddenly began
to speak fluent German,</i>

59:51.338 --> 59:54.012
<i>though he had never studied
the language.</i>

59:54.174 --> 59:55.721
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS GERMAN)</font>

01:00:01.932 --> 01:00:04.276
<i>He promptly lost consciousness.</i>

01:00:04.434 --> 01:00:05.686
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:00:05.852 --> 01:00:08.401
<font color="#D900D9">(SIREN WAILS)</font>

01:00:14.903 --> 01:00:17.452
Where does it hurt?

01:00:17.614 --> 01:00:21.369
Ah... <font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS GERMAN)</font>

01:00:22.452 --> 01:00:25.126
<i>Conrad's worst fear had come true.</i>

01:00:26.957 --> 01:00:28.630
<i>He was all alone.</i>

01:00:30.210 --> 01:00:33.180
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE DIAL TONE)</font>

01:00:33.338 --> 01:00:34.931
Hello.

01:00:35.090 --> 01:00:36.592
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Who is this?

01:00:36.758 --> 01:00:39.602
It's your son, Conrad. Hi.
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <i>Oh, Connie.</i>

01:00:39.761 --> 01:00:41.921
Where are you? What's that noise?
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT RATTLING)</font>

01:00:41.930 --> 01:00:43.370
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <i>Can't you see
I'm preoccupied?</i>

01:00:43.473 --> 01:00:46.818
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)</font>

01:00:46.977 --> 01:00:48.604
When are you coming home?

01:00:48.770 --> 01:00:50.192
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <i>I don't know, darling.</i>

01:00:50.355 --> 01:00:52.323
<i>Divorces of this stature
can take some time.</i>

01:00:52.482 --> 01:00:57.113
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES TO SHOUT
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)</font>

01:00:57.279 --> 01:00:58.952
How long, do you think?

01:00:59.114 --> 01:01:01.492
<i>Look, I... I have to go.</i>

01:01:01.658 --> 01:01:03.706
<font color="#D900D9">(CALL DISCONNECTS)</font>

01:01:19.342 --> 01:01:21.845
Maybe this won't blow over.

01:01:23.805 --> 01:01:25.978
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> I just saw the most amazing
performance piece

01:01:26.141 --> 01:01:28.076
where a husband and wife
tied themselves together

01:01:28.101 --> 01:01:30.479
with a 10-foot rope
for an entire year.

01:01:30.645 --> 01:01:33.273
It was a commentary
on the modern relationship.

01:01:33.440 --> 01:01:35.784
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> That is the most beautiful
metaphor I've ever heard.

01:01:35.942 --> 01:01:38.536
What happened to them?

01:01:40.155 --> 01:01:42.624
They got a divorce.
Hmm.

01:01:47.329 --> 01:01:49.252
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> I heard you met
with Beatrice earlier.

01:01:49.414 --> 01:01:52.213
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> She was trying to get me
to do what we're doing right now.

01:01:52.375 --> 01:01:53.922
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Yeah.

01:01:56.171 --> 01:01:57.593
Dylan, I guess you were right.

01:01:57.756 --> 01:01:59.383
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> About what?

01:01:59.549 --> 01:02:02.553
Sometimes I am my own worst enemy.

01:02:04.554 --> 01:02:07.148
<font color="#D900D9">(DYLAN SIGHS)</font>

01:02:07.307 --> 01:02:09.856
What happened to your face?

01:02:13.230 --> 01:02:14.903
I got hit by a truck.

01:02:15.065 --> 01:02:16.692
Mmm.

01:02:16.858 --> 01:02:18.735
Zeus is dead.

01:02:20.445 --> 01:02:22.118
"You could fetter my leg,"

01:02:22.280 --> 01:02:25.329
"but Zeus himself cannot get
the better of my free will."

01:02:26.785 --> 01:02:29.254
Hear, hear.
And I want my Volvo back.

01:02:29.412 --> 01:02:31.631
That was just a joke.

01:02:31.790 --> 01:02:33.667
How are things with Jocelyn?

01:02:33.833 --> 01:02:36.006
Oh, we broke up again.

01:02:36.169 --> 01:02:38.922
This time it's for good.
I think she was stealing from me.

01:02:40.674 --> 01:02:42.301
That's rough.

01:02:42.467 --> 01:02:45.687
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> How are things
with Beatrice?

01:02:45.845 --> 01:02:48.473
Not so good.
<font color="#808080">DYLAN:</font> No?

01:02:48.640 --> 01:02:51.439
Well, it's not a surprise considering
what an asshole you are.

01:02:52.644 --> 01:02:56.274
I resent that.
Well, you should. It was an insult.

01:02:56.439 --> 01:02:59.238
You're not still mad at me,
are you?

01:02:59.401 --> 01:03:01.119
Not at all.

01:03:04.739 --> 01:03:06.412
Maybe a little.

01:03:06.574 --> 01:03:10.579
I really thought
Beatrice and I were gonna last.

01:03:11.955 --> 01:03:14.378
What is it?

01:03:16.334 --> 01:03:17.802
Hi.
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Hi.

01:03:17.961 --> 01:03:22.933
Now, you two seem like
fans of literature.

01:03:23.091 --> 01:03:27.221
I have got a very impressive library
at my apartment.

01:03:27.387 --> 01:03:28.889
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Really?

01:03:29.055 --> 01:03:33.526
Mm-hm. You wanna see
my Balzac collection?

01:03:33.685 --> 01:03:35.983
You sure you don't wanna
do anything?

01:03:36.146 --> 01:03:37.989
No, I can't, sorry.

01:03:38.148 --> 01:03:41.243
It would be a misrepresentation
of how I feel inside.

01:03:42.819 --> 01:03:45.538
I... I don't even know what that means.

01:03:46.573 --> 01:03:49.452
Well, that's exactly the problem.

01:04:02.839 --> 01:04:05.513
You can, um, keep the Volvo.

01:04:29.783 --> 01:04:33.663
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGS)</font>

01:04:42.253 --> 01:04:46.975
Beatrice, it's Conrad.
Give me a call. Call me back.

01:04:49.511 --> 01:04:52.640
<font color="#D900D9">(DREAMY MUSIC)</font>

01:04:54.057 --> 01:04:57.106
<font color="#808080">DOCTOR:</font> What do you see, Conrad?

01:04:57.268 --> 01:04:58.941
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Sex.

01:05:00.438 --> 01:05:02.031
And now?

01:05:02.190 --> 01:05:07.117
Beatrice. I mean, sex.
I mean, wait, Beatrice.

01:05:10.615 --> 01:05:12.993
Now?

01:05:13.159 --> 01:05:15.002
Sex.

01:05:16.996 --> 01:05:19.749
This isn't healthy, Conrad.

01:05:19.916 --> 01:05:22.465
I know that.

01:05:23.628 --> 01:05:28.384
<i>Meanwhile, Beatrice visited
her Upper West Side mystic</i>

01:05:28.550 --> 01:05:31.645
<i>in an attempt to find similar answers
to her quandary.</i>

01:05:33.596 --> 01:05:39.023
<i>Unfortunately, her prospects
were less than ideal.</i>

01:05:40.437 --> 01:05:43.532
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> I mean, I've only just moved
in, she's already kicked me out.

01:05:43.690 --> 01:05:47.160
I don't know.
I don't know what to do. <font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:05:47.318 --> 01:05:51.494
<font color="#808080">DOCTOR:</font> Sometimes we have to make
sacrifices for the ones we love.

01:05:51.656 --> 01:05:54.535
This literary moral code of yours
is completely unrealistic.

01:05:54.701 --> 01:05:58.331
This isn't a Jane Austen novel,
and I'm certainly not Emily Post.

01:05:58.496 --> 01:06:04.174
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font> You have the moral code
of a Bolshevik, Conrad.

01:06:04.335 --> 01:06:07.214
I mean, I'm... I'm having
an existential crisis here.

01:06:07.380 --> 01:06:10.304
I can't stop thinking about her.
I think I need to see a doctor.

01:06:11.718 --> 01:06:13.345
<font color="#D900D9">(DOORBELL BUZZES)</font>

01:06:13.511 --> 01:06:16.230
<font color="#808080">DOCTOR:</font> Conrad, I am a doctor.

01:06:20.268 --> 01:06:25.024
Beatrice? Beatrice?

01:06:30.612 --> 01:06:36.619
Note to self. Upon a second reading,
my analyst was correct.

01:06:36.784 --> 01:06:40.004
It has EVERYTHING to do
with "Pygmalion"

01:07:02.977 --> 01:07:05.230
<font color="#D900D9">(KNOCK ON DOOR)</font>

01:07:05.396 --> 01:07:07.694
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Dylan, wake up.

01:07:07.857 --> 01:07:10.360
What? What is it?

01:07:10.527 --> 01:07:12.120
I need Jocelyn's phone number.

01:07:12.278 --> 01:07:14.952
<font color="#808080">CAMERAMAN:</font> Allez, Beatrice.
Regarde-moi. Regarde-moi.

01:07:15.114 --> 01:07:18.709
Voilà. Comme ga. Magnifique.
Tu es belle, tu es belle.

01:07:18.868 --> 01:07:22.168
Petit oiseau. Ah, voila. Love.

01:07:22.330 --> 01:07:24.708
Hate!

01:07:24.874 --> 01:07:28.879
Stop! Don't move. Voilà.
Superbe. Superbe.

01:07:29.045 --> 01:07:31.523
Splendide. Encore une, encore une.
Une derniére pour la route.

01:07:31.548 --> 01:07:35.143
<font color="#D900D9">(<i>AIR ON THE G STRING</i>
BY BACH PLAYS)</font>

01:07:35.301 --> 01:07:40.102
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> OK, let's...
let's take a break. Hmm?

01:07:50.984 --> 01:07:52.452
Hi.

01:07:52.610 --> 01:07:55.534
What happened to your head?

01:07:55.697 --> 01:07:57.791
I got hit by a truck.

01:07:57.949 --> 01:07:59.872
Yeah.

01:08:01.744 --> 01:08:03.496
I like this music selection.

01:08:03.663 --> 01:08:07.463
Whose is it?
What are you doing here?

01:08:09.085 --> 01:08:13.215
I'm quitting. The whole act.

01:08:15.383 --> 01:08:19.854
Well, it wasn't the act that bothered
me. It was the cover-up.

01:08:20.013 --> 01:08:24.393
Well, the act was the cover-up.
I have to go back to work.

01:08:24.559 --> 01:08:26.857
Can I have one hour?
I just need one hour.

01:08:27.020 --> 01:08:29.944
OK. One hour.
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Yeah.

01:08:30.106 --> 01:08:32.108
Thanks. I'll be right here.

01:08:39.282 --> 01:08:42.411
<font color="#D900D9">(KEYS JINGLE, DOOR OPENS)</font>

01:08:46.038 --> 01:08:49.542
I hate surprises.
You're gonna like this one.

01:08:54.380 --> 01:08:56.348
I don't understand.
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> It's for both of us.

01:08:56.506 --> 01:08:58.305
Don't get too excited.
It's just a rental.

01:08:58.468 --> 01:09:00.937
You didn't?

01:09:01.095 --> 01:09:03.268
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> I did.

01:09:12.564 --> 01:09:14.363
How?

01:09:22.283 --> 01:09:24.411
There's no leaks in the ceiling.

01:09:26.245 --> 01:09:28.714
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR SQUEAKS)</font>
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Got his-and-her bathrooms.

01:09:30.707 --> 01:09:32.836
This water is not brown.

01:09:38.383 --> 01:09:40.680
What's wrong?

01:09:42.804 --> 01:09:45.057
Nothing.

01:09:46.974 --> 01:09:51.319
So did you actually go to the Picasso
retrospective last week?

01:09:51.479 --> 01:09:53.527
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> It was horrid.
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> I know.

01:09:53.689 --> 01:09:58.742
I'm sorry, but I find his work
pretentious and adolescent.

01:09:58.903 --> 01:10:02.908
You know, if people
just sort of take a step back...

01:10:03.074 --> 01:10:06.453
Do you ever notice that the people
who make fun of people

01:10:06.619 --> 01:10:09.372
for being pretentious are
usually the pretentious ones?

01:10:09.539 --> 01:10:11.917
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> It's just Duchamp
but without the wit.

01:10:12.083 --> 01:10:14.461
<font color="#D900D9">(WOMAN LAUGHS)</font>

01:10:14.627 --> 01:10:18.803
You ever noticed how people
only lash out on others

01:10:18.965 --> 01:10:23.687
because they're afraid of what
they see because they see themselves?

01:10:27.348 --> 01:10:28.975
What if I tell you "I love you"?

01:10:29.142 --> 01:10:31.645
Does that mean
I actually love myself?

01:10:33.563 --> 01:10:35.156
Exactly.

01:10:36.607 --> 01:10:38.530
I love you.

01:10:41.195 --> 01:10:43.744
I love you too.

01:10:54.083 --> 01:10:59.465
<i>It was at that moment Conrad
and Beatrice knew that it was over.</i>

01:10:59.630 --> 01:11:02.554
<i>Beatrice couldn't help
but feel sympathy for Conrad.</i>

01:11:02.717 --> 01:11:06.062
<i>Not love but sympathy.</i>

01:11:06.220 --> 01:11:09.599
<i>One can often get confused
for the other.</i>

01:11:11.934 --> 01:11:14.733
<i>As the two exited the station,</i>

01:11:14.896 --> 01:11:17.866
<i>they waved goodbye
to one another as usual.</i>

01:11:19.984 --> 01:11:23.989
<i>It would be the last time
they would ever see each other.</i>

01:11:34.707 --> 01:11:37.631
<font color="#D900D9">(<i>MOONLIGHT BECOMES YOU</i>
BY CHET BAKER PLAYS)</font>

01:11:37.794 --> 01:11:40.468
<i>It seemed there was
an unavoidable distinction</i>

01:11:40.630 --> 01:11:44.305
<i>between Conrad and Beatrice that
had rendered them incompatible.</i>

01:11:44.467 --> 01:11:49.314
<i>She was a hopeless romantic,
and he was romantically hopeless.</i>

01:11:49.472 --> 01:11:53.568
<i>By the week's end,
Conrad had received a telegram</i>

01:11:53.726 --> 01:11:56.229
<i>informing him of his parents'
reconciliation.</i>

01:11:56.395 --> 01:11:59.148
<i>Their week-long divorce
had grown tiresome,</i>

01:11:59.315 --> 01:12:03.616
<i>and they were to return home
in two days time.</i>

01:12:03.778 --> 01:12:06.406
<i>As much as Beatrice had tried,</i>

01:12:06.572 --> 01:12:09.951
<i>she was unable to forget
Conrad's actions.</i>

01:12:11.536 --> 01:12:13.504
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

01:12:22.296 --> 01:12:26.096
Note to self. See doctor
about possible brain tumour.

01:12:26.259 --> 01:12:30.480
<i>Conrad went on to keep the empty
apartment as a sort of metaphor</i>

01:12:30.638 --> 01:12:32.936
<i>for the void left by Beatrice.</i>

01:12:34.725 --> 01:12:37.695
<i>He told no one of its existence.</i>

01:12:39.355 --> 01:12:42.529
<i>It wasn't till years later
that Conrad would realise</i>

01:12:42.692 --> 01:12:44.990
<i>love was just like communism -</i>

01:12:45.152 --> 01:12:48.452
<i>it was a great idea
but never quite worked out.</i>

01:12:48.614 --> 01:12:52.619
<i>Conrad may have told others that
he was in search of a girlfriend,</i>

01:12:52.785 --> 01:12:55.709
<i>a future wife,
but it was merely rhetoric.</i>

01:12:55.872 --> 01:13:00.719
<i>Conrad's search was for an idyllic
beauty he would never attain.</i>

01:13:00.877 --> 01:13:04.131
<i>Conrad often became attached
to the idea of something</i>

01:13:04.297 --> 01:13:08.643
<i>and not the actual thing itself.</i>

01:13:08.801 --> 01:13:12.681
<i>Back in the Valmont with
his credit cards once again active,</i>

01:13:12.847 --> 01:13:15.771
<i>Conrad resumed the life
he was accustomed to living.</i>

01:13:15.933 --> 01:13:17.935
<i>But something was different.</i>

01:13:18.102 --> 01:13:20.150
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Like this one right there.
Get that one.

01:13:21.439 --> 01:13:24.067
I missed it.

01:13:24.233 --> 01:13:27.453
OK, why the hell
are we fishing with spears?

01:13:32.199 --> 01:13:35.328
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSICIANS PLAY
<i>AIR ON THE G STRING</i>)</font>

01:13:49.091 --> 01:13:50.889
What's wrong?

01:13:55.181 --> 01:13:58.151
It's been a long week.

01:13:58.309 --> 01:14:01.779
<i>With the matriarch of the Valmont
household once again home,</i>

01:14:01.938 --> 01:14:06.489
<i>Conrad was able to let out
a decade of emotions and fears</i>

01:14:06.651 --> 01:14:09.575
<i>for she had long been
the only person</i>

01:14:09.737 --> 01:14:11.785
<i>that he would truly confide in.</i>

01:14:15.326 --> 01:14:18.375
I think there's something wrong
with me.

01:14:18.537 --> 01:14:19.937
<i>In an attempt to change his ways...</i>

01:14:20.081 --> 01:14:21.458
Ding-dong.

01:14:21.624 --> 01:14:23.592
<i>...Conrad started down the road
to redemption</i>

01:14:23.751 --> 01:14:27.346
<i>with the simple gesture
of quitting cigarettes,</i>

01:14:27.505 --> 01:14:30.725
<i>of getting his father's
Austin-Healey out of hock,</i>

01:14:30.883 --> 01:14:33.853
<i>and on one spring afternoon
while Dylan was out,</i>

01:14:34.011 --> 01:14:37.606
<i>Conrad snuck into his friend's apartment
to finally repay him.</i>

01:14:37.765 --> 01:14:41.861
<i>He not only monetarily compensated
Dylan for his loan</i>

01:14:42.019 --> 01:14:45.148
<i>but also included the keys
to his Volvo</i>

01:14:45.314 --> 01:14:48.989
<i>and an inflation-adjusted interest
of 20%.</i>

01:14:50.444 --> 01:14:54.620
These are classic symptoms.
I think you're a closet agoraphobic.

01:14:54.782 --> 01:14:57.456
<font color="#D900D9">(KNOCKS ON DOOR)</font>
I'm terminating our sessions.

01:14:57.618 --> 01:15:00.212
Conrad, can we talk
about this later?

01:15:00.371 --> 01:15:01.748
I'm in the middle of a session.

01:15:01.914 --> 01:15:04.042
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> I don't care.
I'm getting worse.

01:15:04.208 --> 01:15:06.586
Beatrice broke up with me,
and I got hit by a truck.

01:15:06.752 --> 01:15:10.097
Look at me, I'm a mess.
Why do you think that is?

01:15:10.256 --> 01:15:11.678
Your bad advice.

01:15:11.841 --> 01:15:15.471
Conrad, I've been your therapist since
you were nine years old.

01:15:15.636 --> 01:15:17.321
Indeed... I think
it's all that bad advice

01:15:17.346 --> 01:15:19.144
that made me the bad person
I am today.

01:15:19.306 --> 01:15:21.729
It's going to take a very long time to
recover from this.

01:15:21.892 --> 01:15:23.690
Farewell.

01:15:27.356 --> 01:15:28.949
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR SLAMS)</font>

01:15:29.108 --> 01:15:31.406
Perhaps he had the wrong office.

01:15:31.569 --> 01:15:32.946
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

01:15:33.112 --> 01:15:35.456
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> Hypothetically speaking,

01:15:35.614 --> 01:15:37.912
do you think someone
could have a Napoleonic complex

01:15:38.075 --> 01:15:39.952
without being particularly short?

01:15:40.119 --> 01:15:42.747
I don't believe so.

01:15:42.913 --> 01:15:45.883
What would you call
this hypothetical person then?

01:15:46.042 --> 01:15:47.760
An egoist?

01:15:47.918 --> 01:15:49.295
Egoist.

01:15:49.462 --> 01:15:52.762
I think I'm an egoist.

01:15:54.300 --> 01:16:00.057
I've never told you this before,
but... you're a horrible writer.

01:16:05.561 --> 01:16:07.859
I know.

01:16:10.816 --> 01:16:14.821
<i>After several years of deliberation
and public speculation,</i>

01:16:14.987 --> 01:16:18.241
<i>Conrad had finally finished
his sophomore effort.</i>

01:16:18.407 --> 01:16:21.377
<i>His inability to complete the novel</i>

01:16:21.535 --> 01:16:25.915
<i>had simply stemmed from his lack of
understanding its central character.</i>

01:16:26.082 --> 01:16:30.553
<i>Of course, the central character
was himself.</i>

01:16:30.711 --> 01:16:35.968
<i>The book was published in the spring
and received mixed reviews.</i>

01:16:36.133 --> 01:16:39.262
"He proceeded to wave goodbye
to Abigail as if routine."

01:16:39.428 --> 01:16:42.602
"For he was convinced
that this was not the last time"

01:16:42.765 --> 01:16:44.733
"that they would ever see each other."

01:16:44.892 --> 01:16:47.111
"Harold went on to keep
the empty apartment"

01:16:47.269 --> 01:16:50.739
"as sort of a metaphor
for the void left by Abigail."

01:16:50.898 --> 01:16:55.119
"He told no one of its existence."

01:16:59.615 --> 01:17:01.242
Thank you.

01:17:06.205 --> 01:17:08.458
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> How do you respond
to the criticism

01:17:08.624 --> 01:17:10.376
that your novel
is inherently derivative

01:17:10.543 --> 01:17:13.592
of the works of Fitzgerald
and Edith Wharton?

01:17:16.590 --> 01:17:18.012
Thank you.

01:17:18.175 --> 01:17:20.223
Mr. Valmont, I'm sorry,

01:17:20.386 --> 01:17:23.014
but I found the book and
the central character adolescent

01:17:23.180 --> 01:17:25.558
and his problems
grossly inconsequential

01:17:25.724 --> 01:17:27.351
by modern social standards.

01:17:27.518 --> 01:17:29.145
Don't you find his change at the end

01:17:29.311 --> 01:17:31.939
slightly contrived
and, frankly, sophomoric?

01:17:32.106 --> 01:17:33.483
I completely disagree.

01:17:33.649 --> 01:17:37.074
I find him quite likeable
and his change rather significant.

01:17:37.236 --> 01:17:38.658
Yes.

01:17:40.322 --> 01:17:43.872
<i>At a matinee performance of
"Les Caprices de Marianne",</i>

01:17:44.034 --> 01:17:47.584
<i>the play which the once tightly knit
group had all seen together,</i>

01:17:47.746 --> 01:17:50.124
<i>Dylan ran into Beatrice
for the first time</i>

01:17:50.291 --> 01:17:51.838
<i>since her split with Conrad.</i>

01:17:52.001 --> 01:17:54.720
<i>This was not a coincidence, however,</i>

01:17:54.879 --> 01:17:58.804
<i>for each had mysteriously received
a ticket two days prior.</i>

01:17:58.966 --> 01:18:02.186
<i>Conrad had sent the tickets
in an attempt to pay penance</i>

01:18:02.344 --> 01:18:04.438
<i>for his actions the previous week.</i>

01:18:04.597 --> 01:18:06.474
<i>The two then went to a small bar</i>

01:18:06.640 --> 01:18:08.893
<i>in the West Village
to speak about the play.</i>

01:18:09.059 --> 01:18:12.279
<i>They both enjoyed it
and had seen it with a nostalgia</i>

01:18:12.438 --> 01:18:14.111
<i>for their old times together.</i>

01:18:14.273 --> 01:18:19.905
<i>They made love that night
and have been together ever since.</i>

01:18:20.070 --> 01:18:23.495
<i>Dylan finally read Jane Austen's
pre-Victorian classic,</i>

01:18:23.657 --> 01:18:25.159
<i>"Sense and Sensibility".</i>

01:18:25.326 --> 01:18:28.455
<i>He found it neither sentimental
nor unrealistic</i>

01:18:28.621 --> 01:18:30.965
<i>but actually quite relatable.</i>

01:18:32.333 --> 01:18:35.337
<i>Soon after their encounter
outside the Hudson Playhouse,</i>

01:18:35.502 --> 01:18:37.550
<i>Beatrice gave up
her modelling exploits</i>

01:18:37.713 --> 01:18:40.011
<i>and formed a jazz ensemble
with Dylan.</i>

01:18:40.174 --> 01:18:43.804
<i>They achieved moderate success
and were happy.</i>

01:18:43.969 --> 01:18:47.940
<i>Consequently,
they both put on 15 pounds.</i>

01:18:48.098 --> 01:18:53.855
<i>Conrad and Dylan continued their weekly
conversations over squash</i>

01:18:54.021 --> 01:18:57.446
<i>and, for the first time, Dylan won.</i>

01:18:57.608 --> 01:19:00.361
<i>Conrad saw this as a sign of change.</i>

01:19:00.527 --> 01:19:05.784
<i>Dylan, however, merely felt
a sense of satisfaction.</i>

01:19:08.285 --> 01:19:11.880
<i>Conrad would go on to donate
a large portion of his wealth</i>

01:19:12.039 --> 01:19:15.293
<i>to various charities
and philanthropic endeavours.</i>

01:19:15.459 --> 01:19:18.383
<i>Unfortunately,
it took losing everything</i>

01:19:18.545 --> 01:19:22.470
<i>for Conrad to finally appreciate
the economic stability he once had.</i>

01:19:22.633 --> 01:19:26.934
<i>He wasn't going to take it
for granted this time.</i>

01:19:29.431 --> 01:19:31.525
<font color="#808080">CONRAD:</font> I really despise
the whole idea

01:19:31.684 --> 01:19:34.278
that by being over-privileged
and well educated,

01:19:34.436 --> 01:19:36.734
that one has to live up
to certain lofty expectations.

01:19:36.897 --> 01:19:39.366
For one, you have to live
under the proverbial shadow

01:19:39.525 --> 01:19:41.823
of said father and/or namesake.

01:19:41.986 --> 01:19:45.866
Two, lofty expectations
can only lead to failure, hmm?

01:19:46.031 --> 01:19:49.581
And three, more scientifically
and mathematically speaking,

01:19:49.743 --> 01:19:52.496
if your parents were a great success,
I think a betting man would say

01:19:52.663 --> 01:19:54.165
that the chances
of lightning striking twice,

01:19:54.331 --> 01:19:57.585
especially in consecutive generations,
is very slim.

01:19:57.751 --> 01:20:02.052
You do realise you're talking
to your chauffeur?

01:20:02.214 --> 01:20:04.308
Touché.

01:20:04.466 --> 01:20:07.891
<i>After the lukewarm reception
of his second novel,</i>

01:20:08.053 --> 01:20:11.557
<i>Conrad began to spend more time
in the country</i>

01:20:11.724 --> 01:20:14.443
<i>to focus on the work,</i>

01:20:14.601 --> 01:20:18.651
<i>for it was only there
that he felt at ease.</i>

01:20:18.814 --> 01:20:21.943
<i>It appeared Conrad's allergies
to grass and clean air</i>

01:20:22.109 --> 01:20:24.453
<i>had been completely psychosomatic.</i>

01:20:24.611 --> 01:20:28.161
<i>He began to reflect back
on his week with Beatrice</i>

01:20:28.324 --> 01:20:29.701
<i>and thought of the old adage,</i>

01:20:29.867 --> 01:20:34.213
<i>"'Tis better to have loved and lost than
to have never loved at all. "</i>

01:20:34.371 --> 01:20:40.003
<i>Conrad reluctantly agreed, for
he still thought of Beatrice often.</i>

01:20:40.169 --> 01:20:43.639
<i>At the ripe age of 42,</i>

01:20:43.797 --> 01:20:49.054
<i>Conrad Valmont
was finally growing up.</i>

